Spec
	// we need to get a session contexty object to be able to do write actions etc
	// Returns a session resource
	$sess = get_session($username, $password, $api_key);
		Uses sp_session_init(), sp_session_login()
		As there is a one session per process limit. This will actually create an
		persistant resource. The resource will be freed when its reference count
		is zero. If a different username/password is specified and the resource already
		exists a error is produced.

	// you need to create a ‘playlist container’ as well, but probably
	// better to hide that aspect in the C for simplicity in PHP
	// Returns a playlist resource
	$playlist = create_playlist($sess, String $name);
		Uses sp_session_playlistcontainer(), sp_playlistcontainer_add_new_playlist()

	// rename the playlist
	rename_playlist(&$playlist, String $name);
		Uses sp_playlist_rename()

	// add tracks to the playlist - we're expecting that the tracks array is a one dimensional list of
	// spotify track URIs
	playlist_add_tracks($playlist, Array $tracks);
		Use sp_playlist_add_tracks(), sp_link_create_from_string(), sp_link_as_track()
		Should the same track be allowed twice?

	// get the playlist URI
	$uri = playlist_uri(&$playlist);
		Use sp_link_create_from_playlist(), sp_link_as_string(), sp_link_release()


Extra non-spec functions
	playlist_name()
	last_error()


Build Instructions

	First instlal libspotify following their instructions

	Then to build this library. In ext/spotify
		phpize
		./configure --enable-spotify
		make
